VANCOUVER, BC – This landmark Panel on Vaccination exposes four lies employed to prop up the public health rationalization for mandatory vaccination: Lie #1: The Measles False Flag, exposed by Jamie Cosenza, legal researcher on Measles False Flags ; Lie #2 – That measles is a “virus”, exposed by Amandha Vollmer, a naturopath from Canada Lie #3 – the #PeaceDay Lie (to vaccinate over a million children on one day) thanks to Sallie Elkordy; Lie#4 – and multiple documented adverse reactions to vaccines proving “safe and effective” a lie thanks to Ingri Cassell. A bonafide EXPOSE!

Serious complications reported by Merck in the MMR-V (ProQuad) product insert during vaccine post-marketing surveillance have included:6
• aplastic anemia (anemia due to the bone marrow’s inability to produce platelets, red and white blood cells);
• optic and retrobulbar neuritis (inflammation of the optic nerve);
• Bell’s palsy (sudden but temporary weakness of one half of the face);
• polyneuropathy (dysfunction of numerous peripheral nerves of the body); Serious complications reported by Merck in the MMRII product insert during vaccine post-marketing surveillance have included:9
• panniculitis (inflammation of the fat layer under the skin);
• Henoch-Schönlein purpura (inflammation and bleeding in the small blood vessels);
• acute hemorrhagic edema of infancy (rare vasculitis of the skin’s small vessels occurring in infants);
• subacute sclerosing panencephalitis (fatal progressive brain disorder thought to be caused by exposure to the measles virus);
• Guillain-Barre Syndrome (disease where the body’s immune system attacks the nerves);
• acute disseminated encephalomyelitis (ADEM- brief widespread inflammation of the nerve’s protective covering);
• erythema multiforme (skin disorder from an allergic reaction or infection);
• Stevens-Johnson syndrome (severe reaction causing the skin and mucous membranes to blister, die, and shed);
• nerve deafness (hearing loss from damage to the inner ear);
• retinitis (inflammation of the retina of the eye);
• paresthesia (burning or prickling of the skin); In the comprehensive report evaluating scientific evidence, Adverse Effects of Vaccines: Evidence and Causality,10 published in 2012 by the Institute of Medicine (IOM), 30 reported vaccine adverse events following the Measles, Mumps, and Rubella (MMR) vaccine were evaluated by a physician committee.11 These adverse events included measles inclusion body encephalitis, febrile seizures, arthritis, meningitis, Guillain-Barre Syndrome, autism, diabetes mellitus, optic neuritis, transverse myelitis and more.

